 opfor1situationenemy {
  coords 1318.714 6.555 3269.891
  angleY -38.5
  m_sTitle "Situation Enemy"
  m_sTextData "Americans are deep behind enemy lines and are taking advantage of our lack of road mines due to recent civilian evacuations. Using the forests as cover, they have been advancing towards Wolf Hill - we are worried they know about the Mi-24P Hind armed with anti-tank missiles that our forces currently have hidden on a landing pad at the top of the hill. "\
  ""\
  "If they maintain their current heading, their company of up to 9x M1A1 Abrams tanks and 2x M2 .50 Recon HMMWVs could reach Wolf Hill (to the enemies south/southeast) by sunset which will be within the next hour."\
  ""\
  "They are believed to know our general whereabouts due to enemy reconnaissance operations. We cannot reasonably expect them to focus entirely on that helicopter–if at all. We must be prepared for the enemy to actively seek and destroy our entire company."\
  ""\
  "They are equipped with high explosive and armor-piercing rounds. Their equipment has superior optics to ours. Current position is believed to be on the north face of Cavalry Hill, grid 034 060, about 2 klicks to our northwest."
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "USSR"
  }
  m_iOrder 1
 }
 opfor2situationfriendly {
  coords 1339.953 6.813 3241.504
  m_sTitle "Situation Friendly"
  m_sTextData "Soviet armor company consisting of up to 10x T72B and 1x BRDM2 for reconnaissance."\
  ""\
  "Though we have inferior optics, we are quipped with deadly armor-piercing, HE, and ATGM rounds in our tanks."\
  ""\
  "We are situated at grid 054 048, on the north face of Bonfire Hill, east/northeast of Wolf Hill by a near idential distance as the U.S. forces in the area of operation (AO)."\
  ""\
  "We have access to more direct routes headed towards Wolf Hill as well as the coastal city of Morton. We are in a position to take advantage of the terrain to give us an edge in securing the Mi-24P Hind to use against our enemies."\
  ""\
  ""
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "USSR"
  }
  m_iOrder 2
 }
